## Examples

### Example: Basic `foo` viewer

```js !viewer of=foo
export const viewer = ({node, React}) => {
  return `${node.value} Foooooo! React: ${!!React}`
}
```


Not used in the default case:

```foo xviewer=meta
Bar
```

Only when using the `!inline` directive:

```foo !inline
Baz
```

or `viewer=xxx` attribute is present:

```foo viewer=foo
Quz
```

or it is an output cell:

```>foo
Qux
```

### Example: `md` viewer

```js !viewer of=md
export const viewer = ({children, node, React}) => {

  const dir = () => node.properties
                   && node.properties.meta 
                   && node.properties.meta.directives
                   && node.properties.meta.directives
.map( d => 'dir-' + d)

  const classes = [
     ...dir(),
     ''
  ]
  .filter(x=>x)
  .join(' ')
  .trim()

  const view = React.createElement('div', {className: classes}, children)
  return children
}
```

